<h2 class="header"><i>6</i>Find the centroid or center of mass of a shape<a class="headerlink" href="#find-the-centroid-or-center-of-mass-of-a-shape" name="find-the-centroid-or-center-of-mass-of-a-shape">&para;</a></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>Given a shape, find its centroid or center of mass</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 class="header"><i>6.1</i>General solution<a class="headerlink" href="#general-solution_5" name="general-solution_5">&para;</a></h3>
<p>If the density is constant, then:</p>
<p><span>$$x_{\text{cent}} = \frac{1}{\text{volume}} \iiint\limits_R x\,dV\quad y_{\text{cent}} = \frac{1}{\text{volume}} \iiint\limits_R y\,dV \quad z_{\text{cent}} = \frac{1}{\text{volume}} \iiint\limits_R z\,dV$$</span></p>
<p>If it's not constant, integrate mass or something.</p>
<h3 class="header"><i>6.2</i>Examples<a class="headerlink" href="#examples_5" name="examples_5">&para;</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Assignment 3, question 12</li>
<li>Assignment 3, question 13</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="header"><i>7</i>Evaluating trigonometric integrals with the gamma function<a class="headerlink" href="#evaluating-trigonometric-integrals-with-the-gamma-function" name="evaluating-trigonometric-integrals-with-the-gamma-function">&para;</a></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>Integrate, from 0 to pi/2 or a multiple thereof, some combination of powers of sine and cosine.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 class="header"><i>7.1</i>General solution<a class="headerlink" href="#general-solution_6" name="general-solution_6">&para;</a></h3>
<p>From the gamma function: <span>$\int_0^{\pi/2} \cos^{2n-1}\theta \sin^{2n-1}\theta\,d\theta = \frac{\Gamma(n)\Gamma(m)}{2\Gamma(m+n)}$</span></p>
<p>For other intervals, see if the sign of the function is the same as in the first quadrant, etc.</p>
<h3 class="header"><i>7.2</i>Examples<a class="headerlink" href="#examples_6" name="examples_6">&para;</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Later</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="header"><i>8</i>Moment of inertia about the z-axis<a class="headerlink" href="#moment-of-inertia-about-the-z-axis" name="moment-of-inertia-about-the-z-axis">&para;</a></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>Find the moment of inertia about the z-axis, given that the density is proportional to the distance from the z-axis. (The formula for moment of inertia will probably be given).</p>
