<h2 class="header"><i>13</i>Surface area of a function bounded by another function<a class="headerlink" href="#surface-area-of-a-function-bounded-by-another-function" name="surface-area-of-a-function-bounded-by-another-function">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Find the surface area of a function bounded by another function.</p>
<h3 class="header"><i>13.1</i>General solution<a class="headerlink" href="#general-solution_12" name="general-solution_12">&para;</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Example - surface area of a paraboloid within a sphere</li>
<li>Probably best to convert into cylindrical coordinates in that case</li>
<li>Just find the bounds, then dS, then integrate</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="header"><i>13.2</i>Examples<a class="headerlink" href="#examples_12" name="examples_12">&para;</a></h3>
